replies.body:
Lets be honest,
Star Guardian {{champion:136}} 
How have Riot not seen this yet

I feel like this years april fools event wasn't handled that well on riots side of thing, URF even though it's coming in the rotating game mode is something that has been tradition since league was pretty much new weather it be talk about it as a joke on the rift into a story about a manatee being hunted down by warwick and turned into a suit which was sold as a skin for 50 rp and had all the proceeds go to charity, into the gamemode itself which was loved by all. When it was announced that urf mode was not going to be on april 1st I and many other people thought it was a joke like how every other urf game mode has been previously announced in some wacky unbelievable way then when the time comes and there's really no urf mode of course everyone is going to be upset. however the no urf mode isn't what has annoyed me the most, what has annoyed me is the lack of damage control there was for the hundreds of thousands of people pissed off at riot for their decisions, there was not 1 riot reply to anything about urf on april, not 1 thread on reddit about it from a rioter just complete  ignorance for the player base. I feel that much more could have been done about this situation and more communication between company and customer would have been well appreciated considering how much of a commotion was caused.

rant over.
all in all, pretty good season I'm happy with these recent reworks and champs that have been released and I am having alot of fun playing with the most recent and most unique champion yet Aurelion Sol. gg rito{{champion:136}}
